An estimated 30 000 people were without electricity this morning after a bad storm knocked out the power supply in the Eastern Cape s former Transkei region but Eskom did manage to restore electricity to tens of thousands more residents. Over 30 000 customers are still without supply in the Eastern Cape after a bad storm last night Eskom said on Thursday. Techs restored supply to over 65 000 and work continues this morning at Idutywa Mqanduli Mthatha Elliotdale Ngqeleni &amp; surrounding areas. 